metadata.name: Broken Window #122
metadata.description:
hello again fxHash 1.0!

I'm back. Very very inspired by the latest work of one of the best artists, jjjjjohn, with his work entitled Broken Mirror. Of course I come up with a solution for those who can't afford the works of the greatest jjjjjohn. This work was created with layered png and templates from PureSpider.

I give the reserve list to those who hold Bottle and Apples. In addition, I also give 25% of the 25% royalty of this work to the minter. Reserve slot will disappear after 2 cycles. So public can have it too.

If this piece doesn't sell out, that's okay. Maybe because my name is not jjjjjohn.

metadata.name: Art For Walls In Public Spaces #55
metadata.description:
Moving inanimate drawings generated with code.

Made with p5.js and CCapture.js. 

Extras: 

s: save the current frame as PNG
3: save 3 second GIF
5: save 5 second GIF
9: save 9 second GIF
You might need some patience for the gifs to save. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Geometric Garden #32
metadata.description:
This is an airdrop for the holders of my fractal drop here at FXHash. The Vector Garden project consists of 8 layers of PNG layers.

The different levels consist of:
Flower
Geometric shapes
Table
grid
Clouds
fractal background
Various backgrounds.

It is also possible to get only one background.


Everything was created with the PureSpider template.

metadata.name: SQUARE GAMES #123
metadata.description:
Quite frankely: a lot of squares

An exploration of recursion
featuring very vibrant color combinations
Interactive

4 recursion depths
16 color palettes
4 expansion states
4 fill probabilities 
4 ghost probabilities 

Press 's' to save a high res image
Click and move mouse to explore
Press 'space' to return to original position
Press 'b' to change color of white cube
Press ‚f‘ for fullscreen
Press 'p‘ to toggle pixel perfect rendering

metadata.name: Digital Organics #7
metadata.description:
Digital Organics seeks to infuse an organic soul into binary code. A flow of digital current passing through an algorithm, rendering a synthetic version of nature.

A few notes: due to its synthetic nature, it will look more detailed in fullscreen. And it is recommended to use this mode to be able to fully enjoy the whole spectrum of details.

A static version can be obtained by using the keypress 's'. 

An additional hyper-saturated mode can be accessed through the keypress 'h'.

metadata.name: Distant Worlds #35
metadata.description:
This is inspired by my life-long love of sci-fi novels and their often fantastical & abstract covers showing alien landscapes and faded, far-off moons

- - - 

Initial pricing:
Dutch Auction - 5 > 4 > 3 > 2 (reducing every 15 mins)

To render at a higher resolution, open in IPFS/full screen and add ?size=2000 to the URL for e.g. 2000x2000 res - higher values will render more slowly

Press 's' to download an image
